{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-challenges-classic-show-tsx","path":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/object-oriented-programming/understand-where-an-objects-prototype-comes-from","result":{"data":{"challengeNode":{"challenge":{"block":"object-oriented-programming","demoType":null,"title":"Razumi/Shvati odakle `prototype` nečega potiče","description":"<section id=\"description\">\n<p>Kao što ljudi dobijaju gener od svojih roditelja, objekat dobija svoj <code>prototype</code> direktno od komponente funkcije koja ga je kreirala. Na primer, ovde komponenta <code>Bird</code> stvara objekat od <code>duck</code>:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-js\">function Bird(name) {\n  this.name = name;\n}\n\nlet duck = new Bird(\"Donald\");\n</code></pre>\n<p><code>duck</code> dobija svoj <code>prototype</code> iz funkcije komponente <code>Bird</code>. Možete prikazati ovu vezu putem <code>isPrototypeOf</code>:</p>\n<pre><code class=\"language-js\">Bird.prototype.isPrototypeOf(duck);\n</code></pre>\n<p>Ovo će vratiti <code>true</code>.</p>\n</section>","id":"587d7db0367417b2b2512b81","hasEditableBoundaries":false,"instructions":"<section id=\"instructions\">\n<p>Koristi <code>isPrototypeOf</code> da vidiš <code>prototype</code> od <code>beagle</code>.</p>\n</section>","notes":null,"challengeType":1,"helpCategory":"JavaScript","videoUrl":null,"superBlock":"javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures","translationPending":false,"forumTopicId":301330,"hooks":null,"fields":{"slug":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/object-oriented-programming/understand-where-an-objects-prototype-comes-from"},"required":[],"usesMultifileEditor":false,"challengeFiles":[{"fileKey":"scriptjs","ext":"js","name":"script","contents":"function Dog(name) {\n  this.name = name;\n}\n\nlet beagle = new Dog(\"Snoopy\");\n\n// Only change code below this line","head":null,"tail":null,"editableRegionBoundaries":[],"history":["script.js"]}],"saveSubmissionToDB":null,"tests":[{"text":"<p>Trebalo bi da pokažeš da je <code>Dog.prototype</code> deo <code>prototype</code> od <code>beagle</code></p>","testString":"assert(/Dog\\.prototype\\.isPrototypeOf\\(beagle\\)/.test(__helpers.removeJSComments(code)));"}]}}},"pageContext":{"challengeMeta":{"blockHashSlug":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/#object-oriented-programming","dashedName":"understand-where-an-objects-prototype-comes-from","certification":"javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures","disableLoopProtectTests":false,"disableLoopProtectPreview":false,"superBlock":"javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures","chapter":null,"module":null,"block":"object-oriented-programming","isFirstStep":false,"template":null,"required":[],"isLastChallengeInBlock":false,"nextChallengePath":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/object-oriented-programming/understand-the-prototype-chain","prevChallengePath":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/object-oriented-programming/remember-to-set-the-constructor-property-when-changing-the-prototype","id":"587d7db0367417b2b2512b81","saveSubmissionToDB":null},"projectPreview":{"challengeData":{"challengeType":1,"challengeFiles":[{"name":"script","ext":"js","contents":"const funModule = (function () {\n  return {\n    isCuteMixin: obj => {\n      obj.isCute = () => true;\n    },\n    singMixin: obj => {\n      obj.sing = () => console.log(\"Singing to an awesome tune\");\n    }\n  };\n})();","history":["script.js"],"fileKey":"scriptjs"}]}},"id":"/learn/javascript-algorithms-and-data-structures/object-oriented-programming/understand-where-an-objects-prototype-comes-from"}},"staticQueryHashes":["3858520367"],"slicesMap":{}}